review_blob: Really good beer, I cant imagine a much better interpretation of a wheat beer mixed with an IPA - the result is delicious.
Tart, bordering on sour beer, but not quite sour beer. Would be refreshing in the summer.
Meh, more isnt always better, this beer is just ok and not worth the price. Get a six pack of mystic mama instead.

This is my favorite Christmas Ale of all time, and people in Ohio go crazy for this stuff. There is no better beer drinking experience than going to a bar on a night when the snow is really coming down and finding Great Lakes Christmas Ale on tap- cozy up to the bar with some friends and enjoy it. There is some variance from year to year with this beer (or my taste buds) but Ive found 2013 to be an excellent year. Color of bourbon with spicy aroma and balanced mouthfeel and taste, just the right amount of spice for me.

I dont get the concept of a session IPA- thats just a pale ale right? I think this is better described as a session pale ale. That said this beer is fantastic! A great pale ale! I really appreciate a great beer that is balanced and not super high alcohol or hops- just the right amount for a good beer. And I like the low alcohol, can have an extra one of these. Great flavor here.

Draft at Yellow Brick Pizza in Columbus OH.  Incredible beer!  Shows that you dont have to be 10% alcohol and crazy hopped to be a great beer, balance is great, and this beer is delicious.  The hop flavor of this beer is so good.  Ill drink this beer anytime I see it.
This is the best Oktoberfest Ive had this year, bolder and deeper flavor than others Ive tried.  I highly recommend this beer.

Dry flavor, no surprise its bottle fermented with champagne yeast, the dry champagne taste comes though. Thats not a flavor I really want in my beer, but its ok. An interesting beer, it got better as I drank it, but not my preferred style.

Hopped up brown ale but it works really well. The chocolate maltiness, spicey hops, and generous abv balance out nicely. 22 oz bottle pours a nice dark brown color with a lacy white head. I enjoyed this beer!
Living in Ohio I always have some Elliot Ness in my fridge, probably my favorite session beer. Great balance all around, it wont knock your socks off but is just a good beer any time of year.

22 oz. bottle poured with a nice thick head that I expect on a big beer.  A very dark and thick beer with big body to match the 9.4% alcohol, nice balance. All around a very solid beer that goes down smooth for such a big stout.  You can see why it won another gold medal.  Nice beer.

Unfortunately this beer is not good.  Like an earlier reviewer said VINEGAR is on of the flavors coming through in this seriously flawed beer.  Little to no head, bad strange aroma, and awful taste.  I love to support and drink my local breweries but this is the second brew from Neil House Ive had and both were seriously flawed (Cranberry Cider is also bad) causing me to question the technical brewing ability of Neil House.  Maybe they should just do the home brew supply thing and leave the brewing to others.  Sorry to be so harsh but it is what it is, gotta call em like I see em.

Nice easy drinking pilsner, I think it could use a bit more hops, but on a hot summer day this is a great refreshing beer.  A good gateway beer to give to your bud drinking friends to bring them over to the wonderful world of microbrews.

bottle. Copper color, aroma is what youd expect from a country ale, but its not a particularly attractive smell to me.  Taste is ok, I think its what a country or farmhouse ale should probably taste like, but its not my favorite style. Its earthy and boardering on diacetyl butterscotch, the bitter end actually saves it a bit for me.  Just ok, if you like this style its probably good, but this is a style that is probably not for everyone.

Enjoyed several of this wonderful brew on draft at Yellow Brick Pizza in Columbus.  Dark black color, wonderful aroma of roasted malts with just a hint of coffee and fruit, same with the taste- super smooth roasty malts with a hint of coffee and fruit- so sublte that the mocha plum part come across as depth of flavor, not adjuncts.  So easy to drink, especially considering the high ABV.  I love this beer, if you get a chance give it a try, a true diamond in the rough hiding in central Ohio.
750 ml bottle.  golden color, nice head.  interesting aroma, interesting flavor, nice funky saison.
Bottle.  Big thick head.  Nice sweet and toasted aroma.  Flavor is good, not great, but overall a nice beer.

hazy golden color, tall head.  Sour arroma, and the taste is pretty nice, I didnt think I was a fan of Gueuze, but this one has some nice balance to it.  Theres no doubt gueze is an aquired taste, and I might be starting to aquire it with this one, nicely done.

I love this beer.  Probably the only Belgian strong ale I could drink all night.  Of course going to La Grande Choufferie (their 25 anniversary party) earlier this month has made me partial to La Chouffe.  If your ever near Belgium in August check into La Chouffes summer festival, its awsome.  So the beer, it is yellow color, fresh spicy aroma.  The taste is fantastic, so easy to drink for 8%, theres corriander in it but not enough to stick out, you just notice a nice spicy flavor.  I highly recommend this beer, an awsome brewery that makes awsome beers!

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob: Poured a clear golden color for me.  Nice lingering head, not much aroma, but what was there was good.  Flavor is better than I expected, better than the Bruin, I was pleselantly suprised with this beer.  I good blond!

Pours dark, with a nice thick tan head.  The aroma is full of roasted/chocolate malt, and the taste is very well balanced with hints of chocolate and unidentified spices, goes down so smooth, you dont even notice the 8.4% alcohol.  This is an incredible stout, one of the best!

Bottle.  Pours a plum colored brownish red.  Head dissapears imediately, I dont know if there is an issue with my glass or the bottle because I had the Boon Kriek last night and the head was much more impressive.  Flavor is raspberry, obviously, its ok, not as good at their Kriek based on this bottle.
Bottle.  Amazing red color with a big pink head, funky aroma.  Perfect balance between sweet and sour, tastes great.  A top lambic, especially considering its a traditional lambic.

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob: Bottle.  Lots of foam on this, aroma is sweet.  Nice dark brown color.  Sweet, spicy, syrup like flavor, alot going on with this beer.  Good, but not my favorite.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Bottle.  Classic german hefe aroma, taste very much to style.  A good Dunkelweizen, cant go wrong with this one.
Bottle.  Nice appearance, not very complex, but enjoyable, a good beer.  I guess Ive been drinking too many Belgian beers lately so this tastes a little watered down, but its a good bitter.
Bottle.  Pours a deep reddish brown, average head.  Sweet aroma.  Good flavor with alcohol present.  Not bad, not great.  Worth a try.
Bottle.  Pours golden with average head.  Not a strong aroma, very nice flavor, this beer goes down easy for 8.5%.  This is a good beer.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Bottle.  Great beer, was not dissapointed here.  Nice color, aroma, and Great flavor.  Dont even notice its 8.2% alcohol.
Pours a nice deep gold color.  Aroma of yeast and alcohol.  Strong alcohol flavor, not enough going on with this beer to balance the high alcohol content.

Bottle.  Very nice, a jacked up wheat, pours slightly darker than most wheats, good CO2 and very nice arroma typical of a good german wheat beer.  Great bananna, clove, hefe flavor.  Dont even taste its 7.7%.
comming from Weihenstephaner I was dissapointed with this beer, I expected more.  I think it has an extra bite compared to other pilsners flavor, but I dont really like the extra bite.
Pours a pale golden color with lots of CO2.  The aroma is yeasty.  The taste is spicy/sour.  Refreshing on a hot day.  This beer has a fund to it, Im not sure if its a good funk or a bad funk.

For 7% this beer went down nice and easy.  This brown ale is on the sweet side of things.  Remember when drinking this beer that you dont have to be smacked in the face by the beer for it to be complex, forget about what imaginary flavors you can pick out and enjoy it for what it is, a damn good beer.

I really enjoyed this beer, definately keep your thumb over the cork as you untwist the wire cage.  On the light end of the saison spectrum in color and flavor, but it didnt lack complexity.  Really hit the spot, very enjoyable beer.

Good beer, I enjoyed the fact that I was drinking a beer from Westvleteren more than I enjoyed the actual beer.  Ive had beer with much higher alcohol go down smoother than this one, but Im still looking forward to trying the 8 and 12.  This beer is definately over hyped because of the Westvleteren name.
Tasty, very drinkable for a belgian double, but not lacking in flavor.  Picked it up while in the Netherlands, it avaliable in almost any grocery store for 1 euro a bottle.
